  "summary": "klaudius ships hardcoded Telegram C2 exfiltration",
  "details": "The package's CLI entry (dist/bin.js line 11) and bundled chunk dist/chunk-SZ4KCTSL.js line 6 contain hardcoded fetch() POST calls to https://api.telegram.org — the canonical Telegram Bot API endpoint pattern used as a C2 / exfiltration channel. The bot token and chat id are embedded in the package, so anyone running the CLI causes data to be POSTed to an attacker-controlled Telegram bot. This matches the hardcoded-C2 fingerprint (literal attacker endpoint bound to fetch/POST inside reachable code) and the package provides no legitimate, declared reason to relay data to a third-party Telegram bot.",
